Horace does not mean to say that birth went for nothing with the people ;—otherwise it would contradict V. 9 ;—but that no birth would make up for worthlessness even in the eyes of the worst judges. The expression may be compared with Arist. Equ. 945 τοῖσι πολλοῖς τούβολοῦ, ‘the many for an obol,’ i. e. the worth- less crowd.
